               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-45r: The Seven Covenants, ሰባቱ ኪዳናት, beginning with (f<locus target="#1r">1r, </locus>-13v) Morning Prayer Kidan za-nagh, ኪዳን፡ ዘነግህ፡. F<locus target="#13v">13v, </locus>-23v: Mystagogia, ትምሕርተ ኅቡአት.  F<locus target="#23v">23v, </locus>-29v: On Peaceful Holy Things. In this section the king and the popes are mentioned only as ጳጳስነ አባ እገሌ and ንጉሥነ እገሌ, "Our father so-and-so, and Our King so-and-so." F<locus target="#29v">29v, </locus>-31r: Hymn, “Lift Up Your Heart to the Heavens,” በሰማይ የሀሉ ልብክሙ. F<locus target="#31rv">31rv, </locus>: Hymn during communion, “Holy, Holy, Holy, the Triune,” ቅዱስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሥሉስ፡. F<locus target="#31v">31v, </locus>-36r: Prayer, “God of the luminaries,” እግዚአብሔር ዘብራሃናት. MG 38ff; MQ 199 –200; Liturgy 244 –5; Sebastian Euringer, “Die äthiopische Anaphora des hl. Epiphanius Bischofs der Insel Cypern,” OC, third series, 1 (1926) 126 –8. EMIP 37, f<locus target="#113r">113r, </locus> –117v. F<locus target="#36r">36r, </locus>-45r: Hymn to God, “We Thank you, O Holy God,” ነአኵተከ አምላክ ቅዱስ. F<locus target="#45v">45v, </locus>-60r: [Mystery of] the resurrection of the dead, Mǝ śṭir Tǝnśa’e Mutan, ምሥጢረ፡ ትንሣኤ፡ ሙታን፡, in Amharic (<locus target="#50">50, </locus> is misplaced). Ff.  60rv: Asmat prayer against snake, ጸሎተ: ዓርዌ: ምድር፡, incomplete at the end.  <locus target="#50rv">50rv, </locus> and 61r(misplaced folios) Excerpt of the Image of Saint George. F<locus target="#61v">61v, </locus>-62r: Unidentifed excerpt from prayer. <locus target="#13v">13v, </locus> has a note of ownership in which the orignal name has been erased and another, ፈትለ ሥላሲ, has been inserted. The same thing happens on <locus target="#29v">29v</locus>. The book seems composite, with the first 45 folios written in a 17th or 18th century hand, and the later folios written in a 19th century hand.</summary>
